definitions: (oma-). MY BACK ACHES Etambo randje mari hibamwa.
I AM NOT SATISFIED WITH OUR BARTERING/Ami hi nohange nombimbasaneno yetu. - PRICE FOR A WOMAN E.G. CATTLE, SHEEP, MONEY/otjikupe (ovi-). Sin. otjitunya.

word: BEAST (GIVEN BY THE MAN TO THE WIFE'S PEOPLE AS A TOKEN OF SYMPATHY)

definitions: SEVERELY -/hombwa. THE MAN WAS SEVERELY BEATEN/Omundu wa hombwa.
- DIRTY/hara ondova. - KNOWN/horoka. - KNOWN/zuvara. - LONGER/nanuka. THE PERSON PULLED THE ROPE AND IT BECAME LONGER/Omundu wa nana ongoze nu ya nanuka.
IN THE BEGINNING GOD MADE THE EARTH/Kombutiro Mukuru wa memene ehi.
(y-). - /kongotwe (y-). THERE IS A MAN SITTING THE HOUSE/Kongotwe yond juwo kwa haama omurumendu.
EVE GAVE BIRTH TO KAIN/Eva wa kwata Kain.

word: BIRTH: GIVE BIRTH TO A FIRST CHILD
definitions: THE WOMAN GAVE BIRTH TO A FIRST-BORN SON/Omukazendu we riveripa omuatje omuzandu.
A PIECE/humbura. I BITE OFF A PIECE OF MEAT/Me humbura onyama. TAKE A -/nyokora.
MY NOSE IS BLEEDING/Me ziza omukota.
